Re: 終り
by blutorange » Thu 06.16.2011 6:32 pm The kanji in the picture you gave is definitely the commonly used form of 終り today. The real question is, what "other form" do you mean? As Hyperworm pointed out, you may be experiencing technical problems with rendering Japanese correctly, as the kanji is correctly encoded (UTF8 etc.). Can you show us a picture of that other form?Also, http://www.kanjinetworks.com/eng/kanji-dictionary/online-kanji-etymology-dictionary.cfm?kanji_id=TONG10 displays a picture of a formerly used version of that kanji. And there is also the simplified-Chinese version, which looks like 终.
