Re: 終り
by Hyperworm » Mon 06.20.2011 6:30 am furrykef wrote:It's not a bug in Chrome unless the page specifies what language the kanji are in and Chrome is ignoring it.This does describe the problem (though not for this page). When coding my site I made sure to mark up all the Japanese with lang="ja", but Chrome refused to put it in the right font without a separate CSS font-family rule.On other sites it also ignores encoding (Shift-JIS) and domain (.jp), defaulting to always using a Chinese font. ._.The presence of hiragana and katakana could also be a clue in the absence of a lang attribute.In any event, I'm not sure how other browsers seem to make the right guess when language markup isn't present (this page as an example), but they do it somehow... <_<;
