Re: 終り
by phreadom » Mon 06.20.2011 7:58 am Mattias offered a "solution" to this problem that appears to work!In your Chrome settings, change the sans serif font to something like Meiryo and the encoding to "Unicode (UTF-8)" and your Japanese fonts should show up correctly again! They look slightly different than they might otherwise, but at least you're seeing the right characters.(Options → Under The Hood → Web Content → Customize Fonts...)Before:
font-settings.png (25.25 KiB) Viewed 3610 times
After (fixed):
font-settings-fixed.png (24.9 KiB) Viewed 3610 times
Hope this helps! Thanks Mattias! This is still a bug, as it seems to affect many people, doesn't work with the default settings, and doesn't do what it's expected to etc. I think the bug reports kind of bear this out? I'd have to read over the bug report again to say more clearly...
